cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as machine translation and post-editing. Additionally, the use of the Transformer model is a popular technique in this field. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve the performance of automatic post-editing. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves the development of a machine learning model for post-editing. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the Transformer model is a neural network architecture. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computer vision tasks, but the Transformer model has also been applied to image-related tasks.
